  "text": "The functions N p i are a partition of unity, as shown in [CITATION_1] . In Figure 3 .1 we present an example consisting of n = 9 cubic basis functions generated from the open knot vector ξ = {0, 0, 0, 0, 1/6, 1/3, 1/2, 2/3, 5/6, 1, 1, 1, 1}. If internal knots are not repeated, Bspline basis functions are C p−1 -continuous. If a knot has multiplicity α, the basis is C k -continuous, with k = p − α, at that knot. In particular, when a knot has multiplicity α = p, the basis is C 0 and interpolates the control point at that location. In the following, we will assume that the maximum knot multiplicity is p so that all considered functions will be (at least) globally continuous. We define the spline space ",
